 "logTail": [
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The kura's count is open to you now: rice in, rice out, and the thin line between the store and a lean winter.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "The outer court is given to you with the rake: the forecourt, swept ground sized for a household five times this one.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "So you put your hands to it. Rake what grain is still whole back toward the basket, a fistful at a time. We reckon a samurai house’s worth in koku — a year’s eating for one man — and every basket you save us is a measure we need not go begging to the lord to make good.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "You can stop now, when the day is done — set the work down, and let the body take back what it can.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Clear it without my standing over you, and you'll have earned your rice and a dry corner to sleep in. I'll make you no grander promise than that. In this house, none of us holds one.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"...You don't shirk the work,\" Genemon says, eyeing the cleared boards and the filling basket. \"The house has had its fill of hands that do. Earn your keep, and a place here is yours.\"",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 3
  },
  {
   "channel": "system",
   "text": "You find a stretch of wall out of the wind, set your back to it, and let your arms hang. The work will keep. So will you.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "system",
   "text": "You find a stretch of wall out of the wind, set your back to it, and let your arms hang. The work will keep. So will you.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 3
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "\"So he can work,\" Genemon says, in the way another man says good morning.",
   "count": 1
  },
  {
   "channel": "reward",
   "text": "You rake the spilled rice back toward the basket. (+2 rice)",
   "count": 5
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Hired by the day, and no coin. The rest when the day-book has a reason to say more.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "One man, name unknown. That is the entry. An entry is amended when there is something to amend.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Straw: four bundles sound, one gone soft. The soft one is entered too. Everything is.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  },
  {
   "channel": "narration",
   "text": "Sixteen mon out. Sixteen back, or the difference in goods, named. The book takes either. It does not take short.",
   "count": 1,
   "speaker": "Genemon"
  }
